      "content": "In X-bar theory, you're looking at how the phrase structure rules dictate where that prepositional phrase (PP) can attach. For the VP attachment, the PP would typically attach to a specifier position within the VP structure, perhaps modifying the verb or the entire VP complex. For the NP attachment, the PP would be inserted lower down, perhaps modifying the head noun or one of its specifiers within the NP structure. It's all about which phrase structure rule is activated by the context.",
